				<p class="about-trext">AKA Gypsy  Vanner  Worldwide.   Has been created to promote the, Gypsy Cob/Vanner. While dispelling the growing myth that, the best of this breed no longer exists in Ireland or the UK. It is not our intention to become involved in a verbal dispute with those who seek to profit from such rumours. We intend to let the horses do the talking!</p>
<p class="about-trext"> AKA Gypsy Vanner Worldwide will present the world with the most comprehensive selection of working and breeding stock on the planet. With the intension of letting the world judge for its self, what we have or have not! </p>
<p class="about-trext"> We have created a global, verified DNA register with the intention of unifying all factions of the Gypsy horse community. Creating the breeds definitive, register and research facility, based in its natural homeland, where it belongs.</p>
<p class="about-trext"> We will offer serious breeders worldwide, the opportunity to breed directly from some of the best horses on the planet. Personally, selecting both Sire and Dam, to create the foal of their dreams, which will be delivered to their doorstep where ever they are in the world, when weaned. All at the click of a mouse! </p>
<p class="about-trext">While we welcome everyone to come and marvel, at the sheer beauty of these fantastic creatures, only our registered members will see prices, the price they will see, is the estimated total cost of that horse delivered to their location, wherever they are on the planet!  </p>
					</div>	
<div class="col-md-12 md-space">
<p class="about-trext">All horses that appear on the site have their DNA verified and recorded on our database and will remain traceable throughout their career. We are here to promote a better sustainable future for both horses and breeders and prevent a reoccurrence of past mistakes!</p>
<p class="about-trext">The board of directors of AKA Gypsy Vanner Worldwide have been selected from like minded professionals, whose first concern is the sustainable progression of the breed. They have no association or links with any other horse registers either past or present.</p>
<p class="about-trext">We are here for the horses, and we are here for you. We invite you to make the site yours, if there is something we can do better, tell us about it. We are happy to listen to your ideas on how we can improve and expand on what you require from the website. To ignite and inspire a new generation of Gypsy Cob breeders and enthusiasts the world over!</p>

</div>
